# Implementation Plan: Fix Theme System & Color Accessibility Across All Themes

The LeadGrowth web application has 5 selectable themes (**Light Slate**, **Dark Charcoal**, **Midnight Neon**, **Deep Ocean**, **Royal Velvet**). However, many pages and components contain hardcoded text colors (`text-white`, `text-slate-900`, `text-slate-300`) and hardcoded background colors (`bg-slate-950`, `bg-[#111827]`, `bg-slate-900`, `bg-white`, `dark:bg-slate-900`). 

When switching to **Light Slate**, hardcoded `text-white` causes text to become completely invisible against light backgrounds. When switching to dark variants like **Deep Ocean** or **Royal Velvet**, hardcoded slate backgrounds override the theme colors.

This plan details how we will clean up CSS variables, theme classes, and refactor all components to rely strictly on dynamic design system tokens (`text-theme-text`, `text-theme-text-muted`, `bg-theme-bg`, `bg-theme-bg-alt`, `bg-theme-card`, `border-theme-border`, `bg-theme-primary`).

